CHANGES0018 - swapFin-ij/ji/fix proved (3 postulates eliminated)

Major changes:
1. Replaced discreteFin-based swapFin with _≟ᵗ_-based version:
   - swapFin now uses `with fst k ≟ᵗ fst i` / `with fst k ≟ᵗ fst j`
   - Trichotomyᵗ is a proper data type (lt/eq/gt constructors),
     unlike Dec which uses boolean reflection
   - with-abstraction works because ≟ᵗ doesn't use _≡ᵇ_

2. Proved swapFin-ij, swapFin-ji, swapFin-fix by mirroring the
   with-clause structure in the proofs:
   - swapFin-ij: match on fst i ≟ᵗ fst i; eqᵗ case gives refl,
     lt/gt cases use ¬m<ᵗm {fst i} for absurdity
   - swapFin-ji: match on fst j ≟ᵗ fst i then fst j ≟ᵗ fst j;
     eqᵗ/eqᵗ gives Σ≡Prop, other eqᵗ cases give refl
   - swapFin-fix: match on both; eqᵗ contradicts k≠i/k≠j,
     remaining cases give refl
   - Key trick: explicit {m = fst i} in ¬m<ᵗm avoids InversionDepthReached

3. Earlier swapAux + cong approach failed with massive unsolved metas
   because Agda's constraint solver couldn't propagate {n} through
   the abstract swapAux applications.

Remaining postulates: fact5 (face-shift-aux step case),
  d-antisym-swap, d² (general), cπ-homotopic-to-id, contractible-with-section

1307 lines (up from 1280 in bck0017). 3 postulates eliminated. No useful work lost.
